init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So they send a robotic probe out to the other nations of the world, all of which have been destroyed by nuclear warfare.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Eventually, the probe comes across a group of surviving humans who have formed a utopian society in Switzerland.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The USA wants to learn how their society works and is willing to offer them a place in the world, but they say no.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The only solution, the USA believes, is to push mankind forward so that they can create a new world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He wants to send some of the best minds from America out to space in order to establish a new form of life, a new hope.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Thus, the plan is to create an orbital space colony, one that will be able to sustain life for thousands of years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A "generation ship", named the "Ark", is launched from Earth with enough supplies to sustain a population of one hundred thousand people.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Ark is headed away from Earth and begins its journey in the direction of the Sun.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Some years later, the Ark's crew begins to realize that something is wrong.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Earth is no longer visible to them, and they begin to experience strange tremors and pressure changes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There is a suicide epidemic, almost everyone has some sort of psychological breakdown.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soon the population is down to one thousand, then five hundred.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So, they put together a plan.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They will begin to search the ship for supplies and technology, as well as attempt to try and salvage the engine.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They have radio contact with the president who suggests that they begin to build the new civilization on board.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are told that they can build anything they want and that this is their new home.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: These five hundred survivors are the chosen ones, and they must begin to settle and start a new life on this spaceship.
